			<deviationsFromTreatmentAndExtrapolationPrinciples xml:lang="zh">无</deviationsFromTreatmentAndExtrapolationPrinciples>
			<referenceToDataSource type="source data set" refObjectId="70b8b0d9-ae5d-47ee-8537-bc6da4b9d859" uri="../sources/70b8b0d9-ae5d-47ee-8537-bc6da4b9d859.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">Huang, B. et al. Environmental influence assessment of China’s multi-crystalline silicon (multi-Si) photovoltaic modules considering recycling process. Solar Energy 143, 132–141 (2017).</common:shortDescription>
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="zh">Huang, B. et al. Environmental influence assessment of China’s multi-crystalline silicon (multi-Si) photovoltaic modules considering recycling process. Solar Energy 143, 132–141 (2017).</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToDataSource>
			<useAdviceForDataSet xml:lang="en">When using the LCA data for the described chemical treatment process, ensure that it is applied to scenarios involving the recycling of Al, Ag, and Si in the context of PV module manufacturing. Use the data in line with environmental impact assessments and industry reports for the polysilicon and PV sectors in China. If multiple data sources provide inventory information for the same material, utilize the average values to align with the methodological framework outlined in the described process. The inventory data sets should be regularly updated to reflect the latest industry practices and input from multiple photovoltaic enterprises.</useAdviceForDataSet>
			<useAdviceForDataSet xml:lang="zh">在使用所描述化学处理过程的生命周期评价（LCA）数据时，确保它应用于涉及光伏模块制造中的铝、银和硅回收的场景。数据使用应符合中国多晶硅和光伏行业环境影响评价和行业报告。如果对于同一种材料有多个数据源提供库存信息，应使用平均值来与所描述过程中概述的方法论框架保持一致。库存数据集应定期更新，以反映最新的行业实践和多家光伏企业的输入。</useAdviceForDataSet>
